I went to this restaurant for takeout on saturday 5/11 at 4:30pm.This restaurant is poorly run. There isn't a competent person in charge of managing what food is kept in stock, what food gets cooked and the order that customer orders get processed (UberEATS also adds another degree of chaos to the takeout experience).  I waited an hour for my order. When i placed the order and paid they told me it would take 10-15mins. 40 minutes later, when I figured out what was holding my order up (no vegetables for the dinners), i told the manager I couldn't wait any longer for the order.  I was one of several people in the restaurant who were upset by the wait time. I asked the manager for my order w/o vegetables and for a partial refund for the missing vegetables (aside: I initially asked for collard greens with my order, they didn't have any collard greens -at 4:30pm on a saturday in a soul food restaurant- i opted for what they had cooked when i placed my order - mixed vegetables).  The manager had the authority to issue me a fair partial refund, but not the will to give good customer service. I had the desire to just start yelling, but not the will to return disrespect for disrespect. There are too many options in the neighborhood for me to subject myself to the disrespect and poor service they're serving up.  Also - their jerk chicken is a chicken breast cutlet with jerk sauce poured on top. Go anywhere else on nostrand for jerk chicken. Literally.anywhere.else.  Also - after i left with my order at 5:30 an employee walked into the restaurant with several large bags of collard greens.

THE BEST MAC & CHEESE & TURKEY MEATLOAF IVE EVER FOUND. Seriously, I’m a picky eaters & I’ve been craving soul food in Brooklyn (which is sooooo hard to find), I’ve really been settling before I found this place. AND THEY DELIVER!!!! They also take cash & card.  They are a bit pricey- but it is soo worth it. Food is set up in a buffet style display facing the server, so you can see (most) of the available items (Some dishes need to be prepared fresh I guess). You are allowed to taste the dishes on display, so you don’t have to commit to buying something you won’t like.  There is usually a bit of a wait (~4-8 min, never more than 10 if you’re only ordering from the buffet table), even though the food is already made. That’s usually because the register is mostly the server as well. Rarely are there a server and a separate register person. I cannot speak on how long it takes when meals need to be prepared for you. But I don’t imagine it’s that long.  Food Review:  The meatloaf was so juicy and flavorful that I didn’t even notice it was turkey until my 4th time ordering it. The Mac & Cheese is literally the best I’ve tasted, better than places in the south. It’s creamy with tons of shredded cheese (not the liquid cheese). I also just recently tried their salmon- omg it was like salmon with duck sauce (but like the GOOD duck sauce that you get from the packets). Usually I like my salmon savory, but it was a nice twist. The candy yams are suuuuuper sweet & delicious. The backed chicken was tender and juicy. Honestly I don’t think I’ve had anything from here that I DIDN’T like. (Which is not easy)
